.SH "NAME"
irq_set_affinity_notifier \- control notification of IRQ affinity changes
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ irq_set_affinity_notifier('u
.BI "int irq_set_affinity_notifier(unsigned\ int\ " "irq" ", struct\ irq_affinity_notify\ *\ " "notify" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIirq\fR
.RS 4
Interrupt for which to enable/disable notification
.RE
.PP
\fInotify\fR
.RS 4
Context for notification, or
\fBNULL\fR
to disable notification\&. Function pointers must be initialised; the other fields will be initialised by this function\&.
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Must be called in process context\&. Notification may only be enabled after the IRQ is allocated and must be disabled before the IRQ is freed using
\fBfree_irq\fR\&.
